caption.p: Three-dimensional ( right) and two-dimensional ( left) closest interactions between active site residues of the human progesterone receptor and some molecules belonging to different class compounds with the best score result. Legend: ( A): Compound 8 (Cepharantine, Class: Alkaloid), ( B): Compound 20 (Triptonide, Class: Diterpene triepoxide), ( C): Compound 10 (Sericetin diacetate, Class: Flavonol), ( D): Compound 24 (16alpha,17beta-Estriol 3-(beta-D-glucuronide, Class: Steroidal glycosides), ( E): Compound 14 (Carapin-8 (9)-Ene, Class: Limnoid), ( F): Compound 28 (Khayanthone, Class: Limnoid).
